\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He grinned widely and sent the bolt zipping into the wall of the room where it dissipated without noticeable effect. He engaged the skill and a second bolt appeared instantly. This one significantly improved from his first, feeble attempt, though at a much greater mana cost. When he fired it at the wall it burst in a flare of destructive energy that left a slight scorch mark on the wall which faded quickly. He flung several more bolts as he further tested the ability before checking his mana.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::0>Mana: 133/238<!$Scr_Ps::0>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Without the help of the staff, each bolt he used consumed 20 mana after the discounts and boosts from his progress and prodigy titles. Clearly the enchantments on the staff to amplify mana were far more efficient than his method at this point. Still, he had his first offensive ability and had managed to create it entirely on his own. He was somewhat curious why the new skill had improved his wisdom though.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So why do things like creating a new ability or evolving my meditation skill improve my wisdom?\u8221\'94 He turned his eyes to the Guide as he asked the question.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93As I explained earlier, wisdom is linked to both your intuition and your ability to understand esoterica. The ability you created was not forged out of your knowledge of magical theory,\u8221\'94 The Guide explained. \u8220\'93It was assembled from your experience with the staff you used and you own intuitive grasp of mana manipulation, ergo it was a display of your wisdom, not your intelligence. Meditation is about introspection, and the form of meditation you have learned so far is deeply tied to your grasp of mana, therefore it, too, is tied to your wisdom.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus considered the explanation for a few long moments. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So if I had based the creation of this ability on knowledge I had gained from studying magical theory in the abstract, that would have tied the creation to my intelligence?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Essentially, yes.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And if I used a different meditative technique, one not linked to my internal mana flows? That might also have a different stat tied to it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Depending on what the technique was focused on, it is quite possible.\u8221\'94 She agreed instantly. \u8220\'93Some martial paths, for example, have meditative techniques tied to the movement of the body through forms. Such a technique might be linked to agility or dexterity instead of wisdom.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That makes sense,\u8221\'94 he nodded in understanding. \u8220\'93So how you get to a particular destination is at least as important as the destination itself when it comes skills and abilities.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Essentially, yes.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks for the clarification. I\u8217\'92d better get some more meditation in, I expended rather a good chunk of mana creating that ability.\u8221\'94 Marcus closed his eyes and settled back into his meditation, part of his mind already considering what he needed in order to create the other ability he wanted.}}